<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFD1FFDDFF39FB0015AFC6E7" pageId="6" pageNumber="703" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD1FFDDFF39FB0015DEC7FC" blockId="6.[241,661,1166,1188]" box="[241,661,1166,1188]" pageId="6" pageNumber="703">
<heading id="D08281EBFFD1FFDDFF39FB0015DEC7FC" box="[241,661,1166,1188]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="703" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD1FFDDFF39FB0015DEC7FC" authority="(HULL, 1941)" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[241,661,1166,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="703" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florida">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD1FFDDFF39FB0016BAC7FA" box="[241,497,1166,1187]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="703">COPESTYLUM FLORIDA</emphasis>
(HULL, 1941)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD1FFDDFF58FB3B15AFC6E7" blockId="6.[144,759,1204,1471]" pageId="6" pageNumber="703">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD1FFDDFF58FB3B16D3C792" box="[144,408,1204,1226]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="703">Larva and puparium:</emphasis>
Anterior fold without extra large spicules. Anterior spiracles with three openings. Abdominal vestiture of long, upright setae. Anal lobe with spicules. Posterior breathing tube orange, not tapering. AP lightly punctured basomedially, shiny and about 1.5¥ as long as TR is wide (
<figureCitation id="134E2A02FFD1FFDDFD85FAC315D4C63C" box="[589,671,1357,1380]" captionStart="Figures 44–47" captionStartId="46.[144,234,1097,1116]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-0@46.[303,1263,195,1067]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figures 44–47. Puparia of Copestylum, scanning electron photomicrographs. 44, Copestylum florida, posterior breathing tube (prp), dorsal view width at TR = 0.3 mm; 45–47, Copestylum vittatum, 45, prp, apical view width 0.2 mm; 46, prp, dorsal view width at TR = 0.5mm; 47, pupal spiracles, whole view from above scale as indicated on images." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443506/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="703">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Pupal spiracles orange, matt, shining apically, and with three encircling rings of openings in upper half. Pupal spiracles as wide apart as a pupal spiracle is long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFD1FFDDFF58FA6712C6C384" pageId="6" pageNumber="703" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD1FFDDFF58FA6715DAC520" blockId="6.[144,759,1512,1656]" pageId="6" pageNumber="703">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD1FFDDFF58FA67157CC6A5" box="[144,567,1512,1534]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="703">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD1FFDDFE95FA66157CC6A5" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[349,567,1512,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="703" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florida">Copestylum florida</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is distinguished by the nontapering breathing tube and the AP longer than TR. It is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD1FFDDFE38F9A8153FC563" authorityName="Thompson" authorityYear="1976" box="[496,628,1574,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="703" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD1FFDDFE38F9A8153FC563" box="[496,628,1574,1595]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="703">C. vittatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD1FFDDFD7FF9A8154BC502" authority="(Curran, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Curran" baseAuthorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="703" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachecoi">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD1FFDDFD7FF9A81602C501" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="703">Copestylum pachecoi</emphasis>
(Curran, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
but the AP in these species is shorter or about as short as long.
</paragraph>
